article.description: Kevon Harris scored 19 points and led four players into double-figure scoring as Stephen F. Austin rolled over Incarnate Word, 83-63 in a Southland Conference battle Saturday night.
article.headline: Stephen F. Austin now 4-1, rolls past Incarnate Word, 83-63
article.linkText: Stephen F. Austin now 4-1, rolls past Incarnate Word, 83-63
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Kevon Harris scored 19 points and led four players into double-figure scoring as Stephen F. Austin rolled over Incarnate Word, 83-63 in a Southland Conference battle Saturday night. The win allows the 4-1 Lumberjacks to keep pace with Nicholls and New Orleans, both off to a 5-1 start in conference. The Cardinals remain winless through five games. Stephen F. Austin (15-3, 4-1) took a 43-31 lead at intermission and cruised. Harris finished 8 of 9 from the free throw line and grabbed 10 rebounds. Shannon Bogues scored 17 points and Leon Gilmore III added 16. The Lumberjacks shot 31 of 70 from the field, 5 of 16 from distance and were 16 of 19 from the line. Shawn Johnson scored 11 points and Charles Brown III and Cody Graham each added 10 for Incarnate Word (5-10, 0-5).
